						<summary>

						<p>Rock behind the Prasanna-Virūpāksha temple in Hēmakūṭa.</p>						

						<p>Harihara II, 1397 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This records the construction of a lamp pillar <hi rend="italic">(dīpamāleyakaṁbha)</hi> in the temple of Jeḍeya-Śaṅkaradēva by the queen Bukkayave for the merit of her preceptor Bhāskaradēvayya.</p>						

						<p>It is dated in the cyclic year <hi rend="bold">Īśvara, Mārgaśira Paurṇami, Tuesday.</hi> The given cyclic year falls in the reign-period of Harihara II when the details regularly correspond with <hi rend="bold">1397 A.D., December 4.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
